{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.36",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 36,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 36",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 36 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:1",
      "text": "And Elihu continued, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:2",
      "text": "“Bear with me a little, and I will show you, for I have yet something to say on God's behalf.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:3",
      "text": "I will fetch my knowledge from afar, and ascribe righteousness to my Maker.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:4",
      "text": "For truly my words are not false; one who is perfect in knowledge is with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:5",
      "text": "“Behold, God is mighty, and does not despise any; he is mighty in strength of understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:6",
      "text": "He does not keep the wicked alive, but gives the afflicted their right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:7",
      "text": "He does not withdraw his eyes from the righteous, but with kings upon the throne he sets them for ever, and they are exalted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:8",
      "text": "And if they are bound in fetters and caught in the cords of affliction,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:9",
      "text": "then he declares to them their work and their transgressions, that they are behaving arrogantly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:10",
      "text": "He opens their ears to instruction, and commands that they return from iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:11",
      "text": "If they hearken and serve him, they complete their days in prosperity, and their years in pleasantness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:12",
      "text": "But if they do not hearken, they perish by the sword, and die without knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:13",
      "text": "“The godless in heart cherish anger; they do not cry for help when he binds them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:14",
      "text": "They die in youth, and their life ends in shame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:15",
      "text": "He delivers the afflicted by their affliction, and opens their ear by adversity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:16",
      "text": "He also allured you out of distress into a broad place where there was no cramping, and what was set on your table was full of fatness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:17",
      "text": "“But you are full of the judgment on the wicked; judgment and justice seize you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:18",
      "text": "Beware lest wrath entice you into scoffing; and let not the greatness of the ransom turn you aside.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:19",
      "text": "Will your cry avail to keep you from distress, or all the force of your strength?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:20",
      "text": "Do not long for the night, when peoples are cut off in their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:21",
      "text": "Take heed, do not turn to iniquity, for this you have chosen rather than affliction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:22",
      "text": "Behold, God is exalted in his power; who is a teacher like him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:23",
      "text": "Who has prescribed for him his way, or who can say, ‘Thou hast done wrong’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:24",
      "text": "“Remember to extol his work, of which men have sung.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:25",
      "text": "All men have looked on it; man beholds it from afar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:26",
      "text": "Behold, God is great, and we know him not; the number of his years is unsearchable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:27",
      "text": "For he draws up the drops of water, he distils his mist in rain",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:28",
      "text": "which the skies pour down, and drop upon man abundantly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:29",
      "text": "Can any one understand the spreading of the clouds, the thunderings of his pavilion?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:30",
      "text": "Behold, he scatters his lightning about him, and covers the roots of the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:31",
      "text": "For by these he judges peoples; he gives food in abundance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:32",
      "text": "He covers his hands with the lightning, and commands it to strike the mark.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.36.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:33",
      "text": "Its crashing declares concerning him, who is jealous with anger against iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
